<br>
*click!* <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www16.brinkster.com/evnhnssn/post/mm01.jpg">www16.brinkster.com/evnhn...t/mm01.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> *click!*<br>
<br>
take a couple panels of your comic to show the time. you can use a pencil. shade the silhouette of the figure you want to turn to dust in *circles*. its perfectly fine if you leave some parts white, some not completely shaded. now there are three different ways (or more) of wanting the dust to go.<br>
<br>
1: disintegrating- in the next couple panels use less shading in circles, until the figure is no more.<br>
<br>
2: bursting- like in the movie Blade, vampires burst into dust. in the next coupla panels move the dust outwards in an explosive manner.<br>
<br>
3: gravity dust- in the next couple panels use less shading in circles, until the figure is a mass--- then make it as if gravity pulled the dust to the ground (you know, like in the really cartoonish comics).<br>
<br>
